<! Horarios Vimeca [2013] --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->
					<section id="portfolio" class="projects_odd">

					<div id="horarios_vimeca">
							<header>
								<h2>Horarios Vimeca [2013]</h2>
							</header>
							<div id="text_format">
								
								<ul>
									<li><strong>Context</strong></li>
								</ul>
								<p style="text-align:centre;">
									<a href="images/vimeca.jpg" data-lightbox="image-0">
										<img src="images/vimeca.jpg" height="250"  style="float:right; margin: 0 5% 1% 5%; border-radius:10px;"/>
									</a>
								</p>
									As a customer of the <a title="Vimeca Website" class="link" href="http://www.vimeca.pt" onclick="window.open(this.href);return false;">Vimeca</a>'s Bus company for over half a year, I noticed a deficit of information on the Bus timings.
									No digital information panel, not even the printed timetables posted on the Bus stop. 
									This meant inability to know the arrival times of the different Buses.<br>
									Similarly to Cantina Siemens app, the information is also gathered online, in this case from <a title="Vimeca Website" class="link" href="http://www.vimeca.pt" onclick="window.open(this.href);return false;">Vimeca</a>'s website (<a title="Vimeca Website" class="link" href="www.vimeca.pt">www.vimeca.pt</a>) where all the timetables and routes are available.
																		
								<ul>
									<br>
									<li><strong>Showcase</strong></li>
								</ul>
									
									
								<p>
									Guiding up on the screenshots below we have that: the first view displayed is the loading menu, where the selected bus timetable is loaded in the background.						
									Then the main view is displayed, and organized as follows:
								</p>
									<ul><ul>
										<li>&#9658 <b>Selected Bus ('Autocarro')</b>: list to select which Bus schedules are to be displayed;</li>
										<li>&#9658 <b>Origin of the departure ('Origem')</b>: the direction from which to display the schedules;</li>
										<li>&#9658 <b>Departure hour ('Hora de partida')</b>: a filter applied to the timetable, to simplify the search of the desired hour;</li>
										<li>&#9658 <b>Route ('Percurso')</b>: loads the route image on a new view, for display on the device;</li>
										<li>&#9658 <b>Circulation days ('Sem', 'Sab', Dom')</b>: days of circulation and respective schedules divided in: Weekdays ('Sem'), Saturday ('Sab') and Sunday ('Dom');</li>
										<li>&#9658 <b>Selected Departure</b>: selected origin of departure;</li>
										<li>&#9658 <b>Bus Origin departures</b>: main feature, list with the departing hour from the origin of the course. To get the hours for the intermediate stops, the Route option must be used.</li>
										<li>&#9658 <b>Additional Information ('Clique para obter...)'</b>: pop-up with any additional information available at the website.</li><br>
									</ul></ul>
									
								<p style="text-align:centre;">
									<a href="images/vimeca.png" data-lightbox="image-0">
										<img src="images/vimeca.png" width="600"/>
									</a>
								</p>
									Although internet access is required on the first use of this application, so as to load the required Bus information, this information is then stored in a SQLite database on the device.<br>
									This means that the information on the timetable becomes available even for offline access.<br>
									Offline access was viewed as an indispensable feature since the beginning of the development, given that internet access at the Bus stops is scarce, and lacking it would frustrate the purpose.<br>
									Similarly to <a href="#CantSiemens">Cantina Siemens</a> this application is also available for Android at Google Play, for free, in the link below.<br><br><br>
								
					
